Open Oracle VM VirtualBox.
Click on New. & give name it as "tycs".
Do next, next, Create, Next, Next.
In File Location & size, click on Browse option(folder icon) & select ubuntu iso file from desktop. Click Next.(If the file is not visible then simple click on create option.)
Click on Start. 
Select start-up disk :- here click on the file icon option.
Click on Add & browse the iso file from desktop. (If firstly not visible then select here).
Open, Choose, start, capture vm...
After this ubuntu will start downloading.
After downloading, click on install ubuntu.
By keyboard layout , select English (US) &English (UK). Click on Continue.
In Updates & other software, Do nothing, click next.
In installation type, do nothing & click on install now.
Where are you? -> Kolkata.
Who are you? -> Fill out the details & click on continue.
Installing started.......
After this, Ubuntu will ask for restart. Do it & in that open terminal.
