$ sudo apt-get update
Enter password :- [123456] (use repeatedly this cmd after below every cmd).
1) $ sudo grep -c "svm\|vmx"/proc/cpuinfo 
2) $ sudo apt-get install qemu-kvm -> (Select yes -> type 'y').
3) use update & cou info cmd
4) $ sudo apt-get install libvirt-bin
5) $ sudo apt-get install bridge-utils 
6) $ sudo apt-get install virt-manager 
After completing, open search bar & type vmm/virt & choose "Virtual Machine Manager".  If a new window comes for software updater.. Then click on ask me later.
After complete installation via terminal, close it & go in vmm.
Go in File & click on "Add connection". Click on Connect. 
Click on +(plus icon) to create virtual machine. Then click on forward. (Step1)
In step 2, deselect the checkbox of (automatically detect from the installation). On top -> In drop down box, select "no media detected". 
In same step, below drop down box, there is file choose option. Select " microsoft windows 7" .Then Click on forward.
Again twicely click on forward.
Click on Finish & then Select Yes.
(..... No bootable device) this will be an output.
